<section xml:id="sec_curved-mirrors" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Curved Mirrors</title>
  
    <video youtube="Mun7c6RB140"><description>Video description.</description></video>

    <p>We can also use the ray model for light to explain images created by convex and concave mirrors.</p>
    <assumption xml:id="a_mirror">
        <title>Parabolic Mirrors</title>
        <statement>
            <p>When we are talking about curved mirrors, we are assuming that we are looking at the section where it is <term>parabolic</term>. This means that all incoming rays parallel to the principal axis will be reflected to or appear to originate from the focal point.</p>
        </statement>
    </assumption>
    
